                                  <msub>
                                    <mi>m</mi>
                                    <mrow>
                                      <mtext>water</mtext>
                                    </mrow>
                                  </msub>
                                  <mspace width="0.2em"/>
                                  <mo>×</mo>
                                  <mspace width="0.2em"/>
                                  <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
                                  <msub>
                                    <mi>T</mi>
                                    <mrow>
                                      <mtext>f,water</mtext>
                                    </mrow>
                                  </msub>
                                  <mo>−</mo>
                                  <msub>
                                    <mi>T</mi>
                                    <mrow>
                                      <mtext>i,water</mtext>
                                    </mrow>
                                  </msub>
                                  <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
                                </mrow>
                              </annotation-xml>
                            </semantics>
                          </math>
                        </div>
                        <p
                          id="fs-idm9602288"
                        >Noting that since the metal was submerged in boiling water, its initial temperature was 100.0 °C; and that for water, 60.0 mL = 60.0 g; we have:</p>
                        <div data-type="equation" id="fs-idm127022128">
                          <math display="block">
                            <semantics>
                              <mrow>
                                <mrow>
